# Changelog Format

## Scope

- This rule applies when creating or editing **CHANGELOG.md** in this repository.
- The changelog must follow [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/en/1.0.0/) and [Semantic Versioning](https://semver.org/spec/v2.0.0.html).

## Structure

1. **Header**
   - First line: `# Changelog`
   - A short paragraph: "All notable changes to this project will be documented in this file."
   - "The format is based on [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/en/1.0.0/),"
   - "and this project adheres to [Semantic Versioning](https://semver.org/spec/v2.0.0.html)."

2. **Sections**
   - `## [Unreleased]` at the top for upcoming changes (optional subsections: Added, Changed, etc.).
   - Version blocks: `## [X.Y.Z] - YYYY-MM-DD` (date in ISO 8601).

3. **Types of changes** (use only as needed)
   - **Added** for new features.
   - **Changed** for changes in existing functionality.
   - **Deprecated** for soon-to-be removed features.
   - **Removed** for now removed features.
   - **Fixed** for any bug fixes.
   - **Security** in case of vulnerabilities.

4. **Footer**
   - Link definitions for `[Unreleased]` and each version, e.g.:
   - `[Unreleased]: https://github.com/blendfactory/speech-kit/compare/vX.Y.Z...HEAD`
   - `[X.Y.Z]: https://github.com/blendfactory/speech-kit/releases/tag/vX.Y.Z`

## Rules

- Write entries **for humans**, not raw git log dumps.
- List **notable** changes only; group by type within each version.
- Newest version first; one entry per release.
- Use English for all changelog content.
